        Tile[] buildPath​(Tile endTile)
        Builds and returns a path from the current position to the specified end tile. The path is represented as an array of Tile objects. This method utilizes a pathfinding algorithm to calculate the shortest or most optimal path between the current position (retrieved from the device) and the provided destination endTile. If no valid path is found, an empty array is returned.
        Parameters:
        endTile - The destination Tile to which the path should be built.
        Returns:
        A Tile[] array representing the calculated path. If no path is found, an empty Tile[] array is returned.
